<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>HYMN FOR VESPERS FROM EASTER TO THE ASCENSION </B></FONT></H2>
<H3><PRE>
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                     G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  At the banquet of the Lamb,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    arrayed in white robes,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    having crossed the Red Sea,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    we sing to Christ the Lord.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                    G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  His body ablaze with love,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    at the banquet, is living bread;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                        G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    on the altar, his blood
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    is the cup of the New Covenant.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                     G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  At the banquet of the Lamb,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    arrayed in white robes,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    having crossed the Red Sea,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    we sing to Christ the Lord.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  On this wondrous evening 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    the ancient marvels are made present:
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    a mighty arm saves us 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    from the angel of destruction.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                     G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  At the banquet of the Lamb,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    arrayed in white robes,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    having crossed the Red Sea,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    we sing to Christ the Lord.
                                 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  The meek slaughtered lamb,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    Christ, is our Passover;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    his sacred body 
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    is the true unleavened bread.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                     G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  At the banquet of the Lamb,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    arrayed in white robes,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    having crossed the Red Sea,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    we sing to Christ the Lord.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  Pour out paschal joy
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    on your Church, O Lord;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    unite in your victory
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    those born again through baptism.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    Am                     G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  At the banquet of the Lamb,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    arrayed in white robes,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">             F
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    having crossed the Red Sea,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           E
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    we sing to Christ the Lord.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">C.  Praise and honour be to Christ,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    triumphant over death,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    to the Father and the Holy Spirit
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">    now and forever.


</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">    G Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A.  Amen.
